if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_TEMP
        || responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_PERM) {
    final String newUrl = http.getHeaderField("Location");
    http = openConnection(new URL(newUrl));
}

suggestion:
After extracting the Location header, re-validate the new URL through isUrlOk() or a dedicated validation method before opening the connection. For example:

if (responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_TEMP || responseCode == HttpURLConnection.HTTP_MOVED_PERM) {
    final String newUrl = http.getHeaderField("Location");
    final SURL redirectSurl = SURL.create(newUrl);
    if (redirectSurl == null || !redirectSurl.isUrlOk()) {
        return new byte[0]; // or throw SecurityException
    }
    http = openConnection(new URL(newUrl));
}

Additionally, consider implementing a redirect chain depth limit to prevent infinite redirect loops.

